AC\n| sec_cik = 70858\n| yahoo = BAC\n| google = BAC\n}}\n\n{{Bank of America}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title=Articles and topics related to Bank of America\n|state=collapsed\n|list1=\n{{2008 economic crisis}}\n{{Members of Euro Banking Association}}\n{{North and South Carolina Corporations}}\n}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Bank of America| ]]\n[[Category:1904 establishments in California]]\n[[Category:Banks based in North Carolina]]\n[[Category:American companies established in 1904]]\n[[Category:Banks established in 1904]]\n[[Category:Bank of America legacy banks]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Charlotte, North Carolina]]\n[[Category:Companies listed on the New York Stock Exchange]]\n[[Category:Financial services companies of the United States]]\n[[Category:Former components of the Dow Jones Industrial Average]]\n[[Category:Multinational companies headquartered in the United States]]\n[[Category:Online brokerages]]\n[[Category:Primary dealers]]\n[[Category:Systemically important financial institutions]]\n", "name_user": "2405:204:a281:829c:b5cf:3a71:88f1:69fe", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eHistory)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bank_of_America"}
{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Turks and Caicos Islands", "text_new": "{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in the Turks and Caicos Islands}}\n{{Use British English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Turks and Caicos Islands\n| map1 = File:Turks and Caicos Islands location map.png\n| places = \n| legend1 =\n| map2 = \n| legend2 =\n| map3 =\n| legend3 =\n| disease = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location = [[Turks and Caicos Islands]]\n| first_case = \n| arrival_date = 23 March 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=3|day1=23|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin = [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], China\n| confirmed_cases = 12<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gov.tc/moh/coronavirus/covid-dashboard/142-tci-covid-19-dashboard-april-28-2020|title=TCI COVID-19 DASHBOARD APRIL 28, 2000|website=gov.tc|access-date=29 April 2020}}</ref> (2004-04-28)\n| recovery_cases = 5\n| deaths = 1\n| total_ili =\n| website = [https://www.gov.tc/moh/coronavirus/tci-covid-19-dashboard gov.tc]\n\n}}The '''[[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|2020 coronavirus pandemic]] in Turks and Caicos Islands''' is part of the ongoing global [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|viral pandemic]] of [[coronavirus disease 2019]] (COVID-19), which was confirmed to have reached the [[British Overseas Territory]] of the [[Turks and Caicos Islands]] on 23 March 2020,<ref name=\"first\"/> and the first death occurred on 5 April 2020.<ref name=\"first_death\"/>\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/> From 19 March, [[Public Health England]] no longer classified COVID-19 as a \"High consequence infectious disease\".<ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef />\n\n==Timeline==\n{{Medical cases chart\n|numwidth=ttd\n\n|disease=COVID-19\n|location=Turks and Caicos Islands\n|outbreak=2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic\n\n<!-- |togglesbar=\n<div class=\"nomobile\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n{{Medical cases chart/Month toggle button|mar}}\n{{Medical cases chart/Month toggle button|apr}}\n<span class=\"mw-collapsible mw-customtoggle-l15 mw-customtoggle-mar-l15 mw-customtoggle-apr-l15 mw-collapsed\" id=\"mw-customcollapsible-l15\" style=\"padding:0 8px\">Last 15 days</span>\n<span class=\"mw-collapsible mw-customtoggle-l15 mw-customtoggle-mar-l15 mw-customtoggle-apr-l15\" id=\"mw-customcollapsible-l15\" style=\"border:2px solid lightblue; padding:0 8px\">Last 15 days</span>\n</div> \n\n|collapsible=y -->\n|data=\n<!--date;deaths;recoveries;total_cases;;;total_cases;+%;-->\n2020-03-23; 0;  0;  1;;;  1;\n;           0;  0;  1;;;  1;collapsed=y;id=mar\n2020-03-25; 0;  0;  1;;;  1;=\n2020-03-26; 0;  0;  2;;;  2;+100%\n2020-03-27; 0;  0;  2;;;  2;=\n2020-03-28; 0;  0;  4;;;  4;+100%\n2020-03-29; 0;  0;  5;;;  5;+25%\n;           0;  0;  5;;;  5;collapsed=y;id=apr\n2020-04-04; 0;  0;  5;;;  5;=\n2020-04-05; 1;  0;  5;;;  5;=\n2020-04-06; 1;  0;  8;;;  8;+60%\n;           1;  0;  8;;;  8;collapsed=y;id=apr\n2020-04-10; 1;  0;  8;;;  8;=\n2020-04-11; 1;  0;  9;;;  9;+13%\n2020-04-12; 1;  0;  9;;;  9;=\n2020-04-13; 1;  0; 10;;; 10;+11%\n2020-04-14; 1;  0; 10;;; 10;=\n2020-04-15; 1;  0; 11;;; 11;+10%\n;           1;  0; 11;;; 11;collapsed=y;id=apr\n2020-04-20; 1;  0; 11;;; 11;=\n2020-04-21; 1;  4; 11;;; 11;=\n;           1;  4; 11;;; 11;collapsed=y;id=apr\n2020-04-26; 1;  5; 12;;; 12;+9%\n;           1;  5; 12;;; 12;collapsed=y;id=apr\n\n|caption=Data sourced from [https://www.gov.tc/moh/coronavirus/tci-covid-19-dashboard TCI COVID-19 dashboard]\n}}\n===March 2020===\nOn 23 March, the first case in the Turks and Caicos Islands was confirmed.<ref name=\"first\">{{cite web |url=https://www.visittci.com/travel-info/turks-and-caicos-coronavirus-covid-19|title=CORONAVIRUS (COVID-19) UPDATE|website=Visit Turks and Caicos Islands}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 March, The Royal Turks and Caicos Islands Police Force issued a mandatory stay at home order and curfew. Violators of the order were subject to fines, imprisonment and confiscation of vehicles.<ref>https://www.facebook.com/RTCIPF/posts/3002672779796133?__xts__</ref>\n\n===April 2020===\nOn 5 April, the first death due to Covid-19 had been announced. It was a middle-aged man who had recently travelled to the United States.<ref name=\"first_death\">{{Cite news|url=https://barbadostoday.bb/2020/04/05/first-death-from-covid-19-in-turks-and-caicos-islands/|title=First death from COVID-19 in Turks and Caicos|website=Barbados Today|access-date=28 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 April, the [[United Kingdom]] send medical supplies to the Turk and Caicos Islands in three batches.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://suntci.com/critical-medical-supplies-coming-for-turk-and-caicos-islands-p5058-129.htm|title=Critical medical supplies coming for Turk and Caicos Islands|website=The Turks & Caicos Sun|access-date=28 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 April, a patient transferred from the Turks and Caicos Islands to [[Jamaica]] for advanced critical care tested positive for Covid-19.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://tcweeklynews.com/patient-transferred-to-jamaica-tests-positive-to-covid-p10579-127.htm|title=Patient transferred to Jamaica tests positive to Covid-19||website=Turks and Caicos Weekly News|access-date=28 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 April, it was announced that the Turks and Caicos Islands now have the ability to test for Covid-19 locally and will commence widespread testing. Up to now the samples were forwarded to the [[Caribbean Public Health Agency]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://tcweeklynews.com/local-covid-testing-to-begin-p10557-149.htm|title=Local Covid-19 testing to begin|website=Turks and Caicos Weekly News|access-date=28 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Prevention measures==\n* All schools have been shut for a month.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.looptt.com/content/turks-and-caicos-islands-all-schools-be-closed |title=Turks and Caicos Islands, all schools to be closed |publisher=Loop|date=16 March 2020|access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n* The Ministry of Health also enacted section 18 of the Emergency Powers (COVID-19) Regulations 2020, making it a criminal offence to spread or disseminate unverified or false information about the virus, whether the direct source of the information or not.<ref>https://www.gov.tc/moh/coronavirus/news/54-ministry-of-health-s-covid-19-update-17</ref>\n\n* Cruise ships have been banned with the only port on the island of Grand Turk shut down until 30 June.<ref name=\"Broomhall\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/elizabethbroomhall/2020/04/17/paradise-lockdown-will-coronavirus-curfew-be-a-boon-for-the-environment-of-the-turks-and-caicos/|title=Paradise Lockdown: Will Coronavirus Curfew Be A Boon For The Environment Of The Turks And Caicos?|last=Broomhall|first=Elizabeth|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2020-04-27}}</ref>\n\n* All airports, seaports, beaches, schools, restaurants and other businesses are closed until May 4.<ref name=\"Broomhall\"/>\n\n* From March 27 the Turks and Caicos Islands will be under full lock down for three weeks.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://tcweeklynews.com/tci-under-complete-lockdown-from-saturday-p10493-127.htm|title=TCI under complete lockdown from Saturday|website=Turks and Caicos Weekly News|access-date=28 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Caribbean Public Health Agency]]\n\n<div style=\"clear:both;\"> </div>\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n{{Coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom}}\n\n[[Category:2020 in the Turks and Caicos Islands|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Caribbean|Turks and Caicos Islands]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in British Overseas Territories|Turks and Caicos Islands]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in the Turks and Caicos Islands]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in the Turks and Caicos Islands}}\n{{Use British English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Turks and Caicos Islands\n| map1 = File:Turks and Caicos Islands location map.png\n| places = \n| legend1 =\n| map2 = \n| legend2 =\n| map3 =\n| legend3 =\n| disease = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location = [[Turks and Caicos Islands]]\n| first_case = \n| arrival_date = 23 March 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=3|day1=23|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin = [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], China\n| confirmed_cases = 12<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gov.tc/moh/coronavirus/covid-dashboard/142-tci-covid-19-dashboard-april-28-2020|title=TCI COVID-19 DASHBOARD APRIL 28, 2000|website=gov.tc|access-date=29 April 2020}}</ref> (2004-04-28)\n| recovery_cases = 5\n| deaths = 1\n| total_ili =\n| website = [https://www.gov.tc/moh/coronavirus/tci-covid-19-dashboard gov.tc]\n\n}}The '''[[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|2020 coronavirus pandemic]] in Turks and Caicos Islands''' is part of the ongoing global [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|viral pandemic]] of [[coronavirus disease 2019]] (COVID-19), which was confirmed to have reached the [[British Overseas Territory]] of the [[Turks and Caicos Islands]] on 23 March 2020,<ref name=\"first\"/> and the first death occurred on 5 April 2020.<ref name=\"first_death\"/>\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/> From 19 March, [[Public Health England]] no longer classified COVID-19 as a \"High consequence infectious disease\".<ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef />\n\n==Timeline==\n{{Medical cases chart\n|numwidth=ttd\n\n|disease=COVID-19\n|location=Turks and Caicos Islands\n|outbreak=2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic\n\n<!-- |togglesbar=\n<div class=\"nomobile\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n{{Medical cases chart/Month toggle button|mar}}\n{{Medical cases chart/Month toggle button|apr}}\n<span class=\"mw-collapsible mw-customtoggle-l15 mw-customtoggle-mar-l15 mw-customtoggle-apr-l15 mw-collapsed\" id=\"mw-customcollapsible-l15\" style=\"padding:0 8px\">Last 15 days</span>\n<span class=\"mw-collapsible mw-customtoggle-l15 mw-customtoggle-mar-l15 mw-customtoggle-apr-l15\" id=\"mw-customcollapsible-l15\" style=\"border:2px solid lightblue; padding:0 8px\">Last 15 days</span>\n</div> \n\n|collapsible=y -->\n|data=\n<!--date;deaths;recoveries;total_cases;;;total_cases;+%;-->\n2020-03-23; 0;  0;  1;;;  1;\n;           0;  0;  1;;;  1;collapsed=y;id=mar\n2020-03-25; 0;  0;  1;;;  1;=\n2020-03-26; 0;  0;  2;;;  2;+100%\n2020-03-27; 0;  0;  2;;;  2;=\n2020-03-28; 0;  0;  4;;;  4;+100%\n2020-03-29; 0;  0;  5;;;  5;+25%\n;           0;  0;  5;;;  5;collapsed=y;id=apr\n2020-04-04; 0;  0;  5;;;  5;=\n2020-04-05; 1;  0;  5;;;  5;=\n2020-04-06; 1;  0;  8;;;  8;+60%\n;           1;  0;  8;;;  8;collapsed=y;id=apr\n2020-04-10; 1;  0;  8;;;  8;=\n2020-04-11; 1;  0;  9;;;  9;+13%\n2020-04-12; 1;  0;  9;;;  9;=\n2020-04-13; 1;  0; 10;;; 10;+11%\n2020-04-14; 1;  0; 10;;; 10;=\n2020-04-15; 1;  0; 11;;; 11;+10%\n;           1;  0; 11;;; 11;collapsed=y;id=apr\n2020-04-20; 1;  0; 11;;; 11;=\n2020-04-21; 1;  4; 11;;; 11;=\n;           1;  4; 11;;; 11;collapsed=y;id=apr\n2020-04-26; 1;  5; 12;;; 12;+9%\n;           1;  5; 12;;; 12;collapsed=y;id=apr\n\n|caption=Data sourced from [https://www.gov.tc/moh/coronavirus/tci-covid-19-dashboard TCI COVID-19 dashboard]\n}}\n===March 2020===\nOn 23 March, the first case in the Turks and Caicos Islands was confirmed.<ref name=\"first\">{{cite web |url=https://www.visittci.com/travel-info/turks-and-caicos-coronavirus-covid-19|title=CORONAVIRUS (COVID-19) UPDATE|website=Visit Turks and Caicos Islands}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 March, The Royal Turks and Caicos Islands Police Force issued a mandatory stay at home order and curfew. Violators of the order were subject to fines, imprisonment and confiscation of vehicles.<ref>https://www.facebook.com/RTCIPF/posts/3002672779796133?__xts__</ref>\n\n===April 2020===\nOn 5 April, the first death due to Covid-19 had been announced. It was a middle-aged man who had recently travelled to the United States.<ref name=\"first_death\">{{Cite news|url=https://barbadostoday.bb/2020/04/05/first-death-from-covid-19-in-turks-and-caicos-islands/|title=First death from COVID-19 in Turks and Caicos|website=Barbados Today|access-date=28 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 April, the [[United Kingdom]] send medical supplies to the Turk and Caicos Islands in three batches.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://suntci.com/critical-medical-supplies-coming-for-turk-and-caicos-islands-p5058-129.htm|title=Critical medical supplies coming for Turk and Caicos Islands|website=The Turks & Caicos Sun|access-date=28 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 April, a patient transferred from the Turks and Caicos Islands to [[Jamaica]] for for advanced critical care tested positive for Covid-19.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://tcweeklynews.com/patient-transferred-to-jamaica-tests-positive-to-covid-p10579-127.htm|title=Patient transferred to Jamaica tests positive to Covid-19||website=Turks and Caicos Weekly News|access-date=28 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 April, it was announced that the Turks and Caicos Islands now have the ability to test for Covid-19 locally and will commence widespread testing. Up to now the samples were forwarded to the [[Caribbean Public Health Agency]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://tcweeklynews.com/local-covid-testing-to-begin-p10557-149.htm|title=Local Covid-19 testing to begin|website=Turks and Caicos Weekly News|access-date=28 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Prevention measures==\n* All schools have been shut for a month.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.looptt.com/content/turks-and-caicos-islands-all-schools-be-closed |title=Turks and Caicos Islands, all schools to be closed |publisher=Loop|date=16 March 2020|access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n* The Ministry of Health also enacted section 18 of the Emergency Powers (COVID-19) Regulations 2020, making it a criminal offence to spread or disseminate unverified or false information about the virus, whether the direct source of the information or not.<ref>https://www.gov.tc/moh/coronavirus/news/54-ministry-of-health-s-covid-19-update-17</ref>\n\n* Cruise ships have been banned with the only port on the island of Grand Turk shut down until 30 June.<ref name=\"Broomhall\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/elizabethbroomhall/2020/04/17/paradise-lockdown-will-coronavirus-curfew-be-a-boon-for-the-environment-of-the-turks-and-caicos/|title=Paradise Lockdown: Will Coronavirus Curfew Be A Boon For The Environment Of The Turks And Caicos?|last=Broomhall|first=Elizabeth|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2020-04-27}}</ref>\n\n* All airports, seaports, beaches, schools, restaurants and other businesses are closed until May 4.<ref name=\"Broomhall\"/>\n\n* From March 27 the Turks and Caicos Islands will be under full lock down for three weeks.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://tcweeklynews.com/tci-under-complete-lockdown-from-saturday-p10493-127.htm|title=TCI under complete lockdown from Saturday|website=Turks and Caicos Weekly News|access-date=28 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Caribbean Public Health Agency]]\n\n<div style=\"clear:both;\"> </div>\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n{{Coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom}}\n\n[[Category:2020 in the Turks and Caicos Islands|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Caribbean|Turks and Caicos Islands]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in British Overseas Territories|Turks and Caicos Islands]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in the Turks and Caicos Islands]]\n", "name_user": "Arjayay", "label": "safe", "comment": "Duplicate word removed", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_the_Turks_and_Caicos_Islands"}
{"title_page": "Red Light (f(x) album)", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2015}}\n{{Infobox album\n| italic_title = no\n| name       = ''Red Light''\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[f(x) (band)|f(x)]]\n| cover      = Red Light album cover.jpg\n| alt        =\n| caption    = Digital and Wild Cat version cover\n| released   = July 7, 2014\n| recorded   = 2014 at S.M. Studios, [[Seoul]]\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = {{flatlist|\n* [[Synth-pop]]\n* [[hip hop music|hip hop]]\n* [[electropop]]\n* [[electronic dance music|EDM]]<ref>{{cite web| url=http://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/21285-4-walls/| title=f(x): 4 Walls {{!}} Album Review| publisher=[[Pitchfork Media]]. [[Cond\u00e9 Nast]]| first=Sheldon| last=Pearce| date=November 18, 2015| accessdate=April 7, 2016| quote=Last year\u2019s Red Light offered a decidedly edgier synthpop sound that leaned more toward the club...}}</ref><ref name=\"bb_review\">{{cite news|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140712235956/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6150400/f(x)-solidifies-brand-of-quirky-hipster-pop-with-red-light-album-k-pop|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6150400/f(x)-solidifies-brand-of-quirky-hipster-pop-with-red-light-album-k-pop|title=f(x) Solidifies Brand of Quirky, Hipster Pop With 'Red Light' Album|first=Jeff|last=Benjamin|date=July 8, 2014|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|archivedate=July 12, 2014}}</ref>\n}}\n| length     = 35:05\n| language   = [[Korean language|Korean]]\n| label      = [[S.M. Entertainment]]\n| producer   = {{flatlist|\n* [[Lee Soo-man]]\n* Casper & B.}}\n| prev_title = [[Pink Tape]]\n| prev_year  = 2013\n| next_title = [[4 Walls]]\n| next_year  = 2015\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Red Light\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = Red Light\n | single1date = July 3, 2014\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Red Light''''' is the third [[studio album]] by South Korean girl group [[f(x) (band)|f(x)]], released on July 7, 2014, by [[S.M. Entertainment]].<ref name=teasers>{{cite web|title=\uc5d0\ud504\uc5d1\uc2a4, \uc815\uaddc 3\uc9d1\uc73c\ub85c \uc804\uaca9 \ucef4\ubc31\u2026\ud06c\ub9ac\uc2a4\ud0c8 \uac15\ub82c\ud55c \ud2f0\uc800|url=http://news.nate.com/view/20140627n14203|website=Nate|publisher=Donga Ilbo|accessdate=June 26, 2014}}</ref>  It reached number 1 on the Gaon weekly album chart<ref name=gaonlp-wk>{{cite web|title=2014\ub144 29\uc8fc\ucc28 Album Chart |url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/world-albums/2014-07-26|website=Gaon|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140731072421/http://www.gaonchart.co.kr/chart/album.php?f_chart_kind_cd=T&f_week=29&f_year=2014&f_type=week|archivedate=July 31, 2014|accessdate=July 31, 2014}}</ref> and had two promotional singles, \"Red Light\" and \"Milk\". This is the last album with Sulli, who left the group one year after its release.\n\n==Background==\n''Red Light'' has a dark and eerie concept, which f(x) said they liked. Krystal added that she liked this concept because she is often given roles that make her look pretty, and just this once she wanted something that would make her look darker and different.<ref name=notpretty>{{cite web|last1=Lee|first1=Seung-rok|title=\ud06c\ub9ac\uc2a4\ud0c8\uc774 \ubc1d\ud78c \uc5b4\ub450\uc6cc\uc9c4 f(x), \"\uc608\uc058\uc9c0 \uc54a\uc544\ub3c4\u2026\"|url=http://www.mydaily.co.kr/new_yk/html/read.php?newsid=201407040712241135&ext=na|website=My Daily|publisher= |accessdate=July 4, 2014}}</ref>\n\nNaver describes the album's title track, \"Red Light\", as a \"blast of urban rhythm bit, reversal in electro house genre\". The lyrics talk about capturing great moments, stopping and reconsidering what is important in life. Also, it is a message, using a \"red light\" to symbolize the warning, that is expressed in an eye-catching way.<ref name=offiicial>{{cite web|title=The 3rd Album <Red Light>|url=http://fx.smtown.com/Discography/?albumID=10146|website=f(x) official website|publisher=SM Entertainment|accessdate=February 3, 2015}}</ref> [[Kenzie (songwriter)|Kenzie]], wrote the lyrics and Maegan Cottone of [[Phrased Differently]], Daniel Ullmann, Bryan Jarett, Allison Kaplan and Sherry St. Germain were credited with the song's music. It was produced by [[Lee Soo-Man]] and Casper & B. F(x) member [[Amber Liu (singer)|Amber Liu]] describes the song's dance as the \"most passionate\" and \"most dynamic\". [[Luna (singer)|Luna]] said that the song's genre fitted with their aim for a slightly intense but feminine image.<ref name=arirang>{{cite web|title=Arirang Pops in Seoul|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y2HgGYTZbW0|website=Youtube|publisher=Arirang TV|accessdate=February 3, 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe title track \"Red Light\" was played on [[Korean Broadcasting System]]'s \"K-Pop Connection\" radio from July 8, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://world.kbs.co.kr/english/program/program_musicplaylist.htm?interactive_date=2014-07-08|title=Play List/Entertainment/Program: K-Pop Connection \u2013 2014.07.08|publisher=KBS International Radio. [[Korean Broadcasting System]]|archivedate=May 4, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160504120719/http://world.kbs.co.kr/english/program/program_musicplaylist.htm?interactive_date=2014-07-08}}</ref>\n\n==Release and charts==\nThe group played their first performance of the album's lead single, \"Red Light\", on July 3, 2014, through [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]]'s ''M!Countdown''.<ref name=m-ca1>{{cite web|title=Taeyang Reclaims No. 1 Spot + f(x) and Other Artists Make Comebacks on M! Countdown|url=http://www.soompi.com/2014/07/03/taeyang-reclaims-no-1-spot-fx-and-other-artists-make-comebacks-on-m-countdown/|website=Soompi|publisher=Soompi|accessdate=July 3, 2014}}</ref> The ''Red Light'' album reached number 1 on the weekly Gaon albums chart,<ref name=gaonlp-wk /> while the promotional single \"Red Light\" went to number 2 on the Gaon weekly digital chart<ref name=gaonsong-week>{{cite web|title=2014\ub144 29\uc8fc\ucc28 Digital Chart |url=http://www.gaonchart.co.kr/chart/digital.php?f_chart_kind_cd=T&f_week=29&f_year=2014&f_type=week |website=Gaon |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140809213711/http://www.gaonchart.co.kr/chart/digital.php?f_chart_kind_cd=T&f_week=29&f_year=2014&f_type=week |archivedate=August 9, 2014 |accessdate=August 9, 2014 |url-status=unfit }}</ref> and the Billboard K-pop Hot 100.<ref name=bb-song>{{cite web|title=Billboard's K-Pop Hot 100 for July 16, 2014 |url=http://www.billboard.co.kr/?c=chart&m=k100&basedate=20140716 |website=Billboard.co.kr |accessdate=August 9, 2014 }}</ref> Several other non-promotional album tracks also charted on the Gaon and K-pop Hot 100 charts.<ref name=bb-song />\n\n''Red Light'' entered the [[Gaon Album Chart]] at number one for the week ending July 14, 2014.<ref name=gaonlp-wk/> The record sold 86,143 copies in South Korea in 2014, the nineteenth best-selling album of the year.<ref name=\"gaon14\"/>\n\n==Sulli's hiatus==\nOn July 17, f(x) performed on Mnet's ''M!Countdown'' without Sulli.<ref name=kobiz1>{{cite web|title=f(x) Grabbed the First Place While Sulli Absent from the Show|url=http://koreabizwire.com/fx-grabbed-the-first-place-while-sulli-absent-from-the-show/15043|website=koreabizwire.com|publisher=Kobiz Media Co.|accessdate=February 3, 2015}}</ref> SM Entertainment explained that she was sick and thus unable to perform. However, when she did not appear in the next few ''Red Light'' promotions and f(x)'s Korean promotion schedule was abruptly cleared for the rest of the month, it led to speculation that Sulli would be leaving the group, or that the group itself would be disbanding.<ref name=kpopstarz>{{cite web|last1=Kuang|first1=Robert|title=Fans Fear f(x) Disbandment Due To Sulli's Absence And SM Contract Expiration|url=http://www.kpopstarz.com/articles/100787/20140724/f-x-sulli-disband.htm |website=Kpopstarz |publisher= |accessdate=February 3, 2015}}</ref>  On July 24, SM Entertainment posted an official statement on the group's homepage, saytating that Sulli had become \"mentally and physically exhausted from the continuous, malicious comments and false rumors\" that had been spread about her,<ref name=kdramastars>{{cite web|last1=Jones|first1=Julie|title=Rumors Force Sulli To Take A Break From Performing|url=http://www.kdramastars.com/articles/30369/20140725/rumors-force-sulli-to-take-a-break-from-performing.htm|website=Kdramastars|publisher= |accessdate=February 3, 2015}}</ref> and would take a temporary break from the entertainment industry, while remaining a member of f(x).<ref name=mwave1>{{cite web|last1=Jung|first1=Ha-soo|title=SM Releases Official Statement Announcing f(x) Sulli Will Stop All Promotional Activities|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/71691/fx-sulli-to-halt-all-promotional-activities-for-now|website=MWave|publisher=[[CJ E&M]]|accessdate=July 25, 2014}}</ref> The remaining members would move their activities to focus on solo ventures and continued overseas activities without Sulli for the time being.<ref name=osen>{{cite web|title=\uc124\ub9ac, \ub2f9\ubd84\uac04 \uc5f0\uc608\ud65c\ub3d9 \uc270\ub2e4..\"\uc545\ud50c-\ub8e8\uba38\ub85c \uace0\ud1b5\"|url=http://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=shm&sid1=106&oid=109&aid=0002837527|website=Naver|publisher=Osen|accessdate=February 3, 2015}}</ref>\n\nSulli eventually withdrew from the group on August 8, 2015, making ''Red Light'' her final contribution.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=241&aid=0002450373 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-09-15 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20150808032623/http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=241&aid=0002450373 |archivedate=August 8, 2015 |df=mdy-all }}<br>- http://news.nate.com/view/20150807n21599?mid=n0107</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n[[Fuse (TV channel)|Fuse TV]] described f(x) as the K-Pop's top hipsters,<ref name=fuse1>{{cite web|last1=Benjamin|first1=Jeff|title=f(x) Are K-Pop's Top Hipsters With New Single \"Red Light\"|url=http://www.fuse.tv/2014/07/fx-red-light-mv-video|website=Fuse.tv|publisher=Fuse Networks|accessdate=July 3, 2014}}</ref> and the album was acclaimed by the critics. The \"Red Light\" music video reached more than 2 million views on YouTube on the first day of release.<ref name=herald>{{cite web|last1=Jackson|first1=Julie|title=f(x)\u2019s \u2018Red Light\u2019 video surpasses 2m hits on first day|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20140704000713 |website=Korea Herald|publisher=Herald Corporation|accessdate=July 4, 2014}}</ref> By August 2014, it had reached more than 10 million views.<ref name=mtsn>{{cite web|title=f(x) '\ub808\ub4dc\ub77c\uc774\ud2b8' \ubba4\ube44, \ud55c\ub2ec\ubcf4\ub984\ub9cc '1000\ub9cc\ubdf0' \ub3cc\ud30c|url=http://news.naver.com/main/ranking/read.nhn?mid=etc&sid1=111&rankingType=popular_day&oid=108&aid=0002329259&date=20140817&type=1&rankingSectionId=106&rankingSeq=21|website=Naver|publisher=Money Today Star News|accessdate=August 17, 2014}}</ref> The song \"Red Light\" was chosen by Fuse TV as one of 15 nominees for 2014's summer anthem.<ref name=fuse2>{{cite web|title=15 Tracks Poised to Become Surprise Song of the Summer|url=http://www.fuse.tv/2014/07/song-of-summer-surprise-anthems#13|website=Fuse.tv|publisher=Fuse Networks|accessdate=July 18, 2014}}</ref>\n\nThe title track \"Red Light\" was included on the lists of best K-pop songs of 2014 by ''[[Dazed]]'' (number 9),<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.dazeddigital.com/music/article/22911/1/the-top-20-k-pop-tracks-of-2014| title=The Best K-pop of 2014| work=[[Dazed]]| first=Taylor| last=Glasby| accessdate=April 3, 2016}}</ref> ''[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]'' (number 4),<ref>{{cite web| url=http://noisey.vice.com/blog/the-20-best-k-pop-songs-of-2014| title=The 20 Best K-Pop Songs of 2014| work=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]| first=Jakob| last=Dorof| date=December 29, 2014| accessdate=April 3, 2016}}</ref> and [[PopMatters]] (number one).<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.popmatters.com/feature/189085-the-best-k-pop-of-2014/P2/| title=The Best K-pop of 2014| publisher= |website=[[PopMatters]]| first=Scott |last=Interrante| date=December 23, 2014| accessdate=April 3, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Controversies===\nThe South Korean broadcast station [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS]] ruled \"Red Light\" unfit for broadcast, since the song mentions a specific brand, the heavy equipment manufacturing company [[Caterpillar Inc.|Caterpillar]].<ref name=cat>{{cite web|title=KBS Deems f(x)\u2019s New Title Song \"Red Light\" Unfit for Broadcast, MBC Still Undecided|url=http://www.soompi.com/2014/07/01/kbs-deems-fxs-new-title-song-red-light-unfit-for-broadcast-mbc-still-undecided|website=Soompi|publisher= |accessdate=July 2, 2014}}</ref> In response, the f(x)'s agency, SM Entertainment, modified the lyrics.<ref name=cat2>{{cite web|title=f(x) Modifies \"Red Light\" Lyrics, KBS Gives Them the Green Light|url=http://www.soompi.com/2014/07/03/fx-modifies-red-light-lyrics-kbs-gives-them-the-green-light|website=Soompi|publisher= |accessdate=July 3, 2014}}</ref> Other TV stations, however, such as [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]]'s ''[[The Music Trend|Inkigayo]]'', [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]'s [[Show Champion]] and [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]]'s M!Countdown, allowed broadcast of the song with its original lyrics. {{cn|date=March 2020}}\n\n==Track listing==\n{{tracklist\n| collapsed       = \n| headline        =\n| extra_column    = <!--Notes-->\n| total length    =\n| title1          = Red Light\n| lyrics1         = Kenzie\n| music1          = Bryan Jarett, Daniel Ullmann, [[Phrased Differently|Maegan Cottone]],  Allison Kaplan, Sherry St. Germain, /  Produced by Casper & B.\n| length1         = 3:32\n| title2          = MILK\n| lyrics2         = Kenzie\n| music2          = Lee Hyun Seung, [[Kenzie_(songwriter)|Kenzie]], [[Teddy Riley]], DOM, [[Engelina|Engelina Larsen]]\n| length2         = 3:36\n| title3          =  Butterfly\n| note3 = \ub098\ube44; ''Nabi''\n| lyrics3         =  Shin Jin Hye (Jam Factory)\n| music3          = [[Thomas Troelsen]], Engelina Larsen, Shin Eun Seung (Hitchhiker)\n| length3         = 2:57\n| title4          =  Rainbow\n| note4 = \ubb34\uc9c0\uac1c; ''Mujigae''\n| lyrics4         = [[Misfit (songwriter)|Misfit]]\n| music4          = Will Simms / Ylva Dimberg\n| length4         = 2:47\n| title5          = All Night\n| lyrics5         = Jinbo,  Kim Lee Young (Jam Factory), [[Yangpa|Lee Eun-jin]]\n| music5          = Lee Hyun Seung, Teddy Riley, DOM, Jinbo, Ylva Dimberg\n| length5         = 3:30\n| title6          =  Vacance<!-- PLEASE RETAIN VACANCE AS THE TITLE. THE ALBUM TRACKLISTING SAYS IT SO, AND AT THE SAME TIME THIS ARTICLE IS FOR AN ALBUM INFORMATION, BESIDES VACANCE IS THE TITLE USED IN RELEASES.-->\n| note6 = \ubc14\uce89\uc2a4; ''Bakangseu''\n| lyrics6         = Kenzie\n| music6          = Kenzie\n| length6         = 3:15\n| title7          =  Spit It Out\n| note7 = \ubc49\uc5b4\ub0b4; ''Baeteonae''\n| lyrics7         = Misfit\n| music7          = Caesar & Loui, Olof Lindskog, Jasmine Anderson\n| length7         = 3:02\n| title8          = Boom Bang Boom\n| lyrics8         = Seo Ji Eum (Jam Factory)\n| music8          =  Eirik Johansen, Jan Hallvard Larsen, Carl Johan Isac Gustafsson, Fredrik Haggstam, Sebastian Per Emil Lundberg, Melanie Fontana\n| length8         = 2:54\n| title9          = Dracula\n| lyrics9         = Jo Yun Gyeong\n| music9          = Joachim Vermeulen Windsant, Willem Laseroms, Maarten ten Hove\n| length9         = 3:14\n| title10         = Summer Lover\n| lyrics10        = Young-hu Kim \n| music10         = [[Amber Liu (singer)|Amber J. Liu]], Sean Alexander \n| length10        = 2:54\n| title11         =  Paper Heart\n| note11 = \uc885\uc774 \uc2ec\uc7a5; ''Jongi Simjang''\n| lyrics11        = Seo Ji Eum (Jam Factory) \n| music11         = Chris Wahle, Didrik Thott, [[Dianna Corcoran]] \n| length11        = 3:25\n|all_writi