xt-align:center\"\n|-\n! width=\"150\"|Song\n! width=\"200\"|Program\n! width=\"140\"|Date\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\" |\"Red Light\"\n|-\n| ''[[Show Champion]]'' ([[MBC Music]])\n| July 16, 2014\n|-\n| ''[[M Countdown]]'' ([[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]])\n| July 17, 2014\n|-\n| ''[[Music Bank (TV series)|Music Bank]]'' ([[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS]])\n| July 18, 2014\n|-\n| ''[[Show! Music Core]] ([[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]])\n| July 19, 2014\n|-\n| ''[[Inkigayo]]'' ([[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]])\n| July 20, 2014\n|}\n\n== Credits and personnel ==\n{{col begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n*[[f(x) (band)|f(x)]] \u2013 [[vocals]]\n**[[Victoria Song]] \u2013 vocals, [[backing vocals]]\n**[[Amber Liu (singer)|Amber Liu]] \u2013 vocals, backing vocals, [[rap]]\n**[[Luna (singer)|Luna]] \u2013 main vocals, backing vocals\n**[[Sulli]] \u2013 vocals, backing vocals, rap\n**[[Krystal Jung|Krystal]] \u2013 lead vocals, backing vocals, rap\n*Maegan Cottone \u2013 main vocals (demo version), music\n{{col-2}}\n*Kenzie \u2013 [[songwriting]]\n*[[Lee Soo-man]] \u2013 [[record producer|producer]]\n*Casper & B \u2013 producer, music\n*Daniel Ullmann \u2013 music\n*Bryan Jarett \u2013 music\n*Allison Kaplan \u2013 music\n*Sherry St. Germain \u2013 music\n{{col-end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{YouTube|iv-8-EgPEY0|\"Red Light\" music video}}\n\n{{f(x)}}\n\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:''Red Light'' (f(x) album)}}\n\n[[Category:F(x) (band) albums]]\n[[Category:2014 albums]]\n[[Category:SM Entertainment albums]]\n[[Category:Genie Music albums]]\n[[Category:Korean-language albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2015}}\n{{Infobox album\n| italic_title = no\n| name       = ''Red Light''\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[f(x) (band)|f(x)]]\n| cover      = Red Light album cover.jpg\n| alt        =\n| caption    = Digital and Wild Cat version cover\n| released   = July 7, 2014\n| recorded   = 2014 at S.M. Studios, [[Seoul]]\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = {{flatlist|\n* [[Synth-pop]]\n* [[hip hop music|hip hop]]\n* [[electronic dance music|EDM]]<ref>{{cite web| url=http://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/21285-4-walls/| title=f(x): 4 Walls {{!}} Album Review| publisher=[[Pitchfork Media]]. [[Cond\u00e9 Nast]]| first=Sheldon| last=Pearce| date=November 18, 2015| accessdate=April 7, 2016| quote=Last year\u2019s Red Light offered a decidedly edgier synthpop sound that leaned more toward the club...}}</ref><ref name=\"bb_review\">{{cite news|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140712235956/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6150400/f(x)-solidifies-brand-of-quirky-hipster-pop-with-red-light-album-k-pop|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6150400/f(x)-solidifies-brand-of-quirky-hipster-pop-with-red-light-album-k-pop|title=f(x) Solidifies Brand of Quirky, Hipster Pop With 'Red Light' Album|first=Jeff|last=Benjamin|date=July 8, 2014|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|archivedate=July 12, 2014}}</ref>\n}}\n| length     = 35:05\n| language   = [[Korean language|Korean]]\n| label      = [[S.M. Entertainment]]\n| producer   = {{flatlist|\n* [[Lee Soo-man]]\n* Casper & B.}}\n| prev_title = [[Pink Tape]]\n| prev_year  = 2013\n| next_title = [[4 Walls]]\n| next_year  = 2015\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Red Light\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = Red Light\n | single1date = July 3, 2014\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Red Light''''' is the third [[studio album]] by South Korean girl group [[f(x) (band)|f(x)]], released on July 7, 2014, by [[S.M. Entertainment]].<ref name=teasers>{{cite web|title=\uc5d0\ud504\uc5d1\uc2a4, \uc815\uaddc 3\uc9d1\uc73c\ub85c \uc804\uaca9 \ucef4\ubc31\u2026\ud06c\ub9ac\uc2a4\ud0c8 \uac15\ub82c\ud55c \ud2f0\uc800|url=http://news.nate.com/view/20140627n14203|website=Nate|publisher=Donga Ilbo|accessdate=June 26, 2014}}</ref>  It reached number 1 on the Gaon weekly album chart<ref name=gaonlp-wk>{{cite web|title=2014\ub144 29\uc8fc\ucc28 Album Chart |url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/world-albums/2014-07-26|website=Gaon|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140731072421/http://www.gaonchart.co.kr/chart/album.php?f_chart_kind_cd=T&f_week=29&f_year=2014&f_type=week|archivedate=July 31, 2014|accessdate=July 31, 2014}}</ref> and had two promotional singles, \"Red Light\" and \"Milk\". This is the last album with Sulli, who left the group one year after its release.\n\n==Background==\n''Red Light'' has a dark and eerie concept, which f(x) said they liked. Krystal added that she liked this concept because she is often given roles that make her look pretty, and just this once she wanted something that would make her look darker and different.<ref name=notpretty>{{cite web|last1=Lee|first1=Seung-rok|title=\ud06c\ub9ac\uc2a4\ud0c8\uc774 \ubc1d\ud78c \uc5b4\ub450\uc6cc\uc9c4 f(x), \"\uc608\uc058\uc9c0 \uc54a\uc544\ub3c4\u2026\"|url=http://www.mydaily.co.kr/new_yk/html/read.php?newsid=201407040712241135&ext=na|website=My Daily|publisher= |accessdate=July 4, 2014}}</ref>\n\nNaver describes the album's title track, \"Red Light\", as a \"blast of urban rhythm bit, reversal in electro house genre\". The lyrics talk about capturing great moments, stopping and reconsidering what is important in life. Also, it is a message, using a \"red light\" to symbolize the warning, that is expressed in an eye-catching way.<ref name=offiicial>{{cite web|title=The 3rd Album <Red Light>|url=http://fx.smtown.com/Discography/?albumID=10146|website=f(x) official website|publisher=SM Entertainment|accessdate=February 3, 2015}}</ref> [[Kenzie (songwriter)|Kenzie]], wrote the lyrics and Maegan Cottone of [[Phrased Differently]], Daniel Ullmann, Bryan Jarett, Allison Kaplan and Sherry St. Germain were credited with the song's music. It was produced by [[Lee Soo-Man]] and Casper & B. F(x) member [[Amber Liu (singer)|Amber Liu]] describes the song's dance as the \"most passionate\" and \"most dynamic\". [[Luna (singer)|Luna]] said that the song's genre fitted with their aim for a slightly intense but feminine image.<ref name=arirang>{{cite web|title=Arirang Pops in Seoul|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y2HgGYTZbW0|website=Youtube|publisher=Arirang TV|accessdate=February 3, 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe title track \"Red Light\" was played on [[Korean Broadcasting System]]'s \"K-Pop Connection\" radio from July 8, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://world.kbs.co.kr/english/program/program_musicplaylist.htm?interactive_date=2014-07-08|title=Play List/Entertainment/Program: K-Pop Connection \u2013 2014.07.08|publisher=KBS International Radio. [[Korean Broadcasting System]]|archivedate=May 4, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160504120719/http://world.kbs.co.kr/english/program/program_musicplaylist.htm?interactive_date=2014-07-08}}</ref>\n\n==Release and charts==\nThe group played their first performance of the album's lead single, \"Red Light\", on July 3, 2014, through [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]]'s ''M!Countdown''.<ref name=m-ca1>{{cite web|title=Taeyang Reclaims No. 1 Spot + f(x) and Other Artists Make Comebacks on M! Countdown|url=http://www.soompi.com/2014/07/03/taeyang-reclaims-no-1-spot-fx-and-other-artists-make-comebacks-on-m-countdown/|website=Soompi|publisher=Soompi|accessdate=July 3, 2014}}</ref> The ''Red Light'' album reached number 1 on the weekly Gaon albums chart,<ref name=gaonlp-wk /> while the promotional single \"Red Light\" went to number 2 on the Gaon weekly digital chart<ref name=gaonsong-week>{{cite web|title=2014\ub144 29\uc8fc\ucc28 Digital Chart |url=http://www.gaonchart.co.kr/chart/digital.php?f_chart_kind_cd=T&f_week=29&f_year=2014&f_type=week |website=Gaon |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140809213711/http://www.gaonchart.co.kr/chart/digital.php?f_chart_kind_cd=T&f_week=29&f_year=2014&f_type=week |archivedate=August 9, 2014 |accessdate=August 9, 2014 |url-status=unfit }}</ref> and the Billboard K-pop Hot 100.<ref name=bb-song>{{cite web|title=Billboard's K-Pop Hot 100 for July 16, 2014 |url=http://www.billboard.co.kr/?c=chart&m=k100&basedate=20140716 |website=Billboard.co.kr |accessdate=August 9, 2014 }}</ref> Several other non-promotional album tracks also charted on the Gaon and K-pop Hot 100 charts.<ref name=bb-song />\n\n''Red Light'' entered the [[Gaon Album Chart]] at number one for the week ending July 14, 2014.<ref name=gaonlp-wk/> The record sold 86,143 copies in South Korea in 2014, the nineteenth best-selling album of the year.<ref name=\"gaon14\"/>\n\n==Sulli's hiatus==\nOn July 17, f(x) performed on Mnet's ''M!Countdown'' without Sulli.<ref name=kobiz1>{{cite web|title=f(x) Grabbed the First Place While Sulli Absent from the Show|url=http://koreabizwire.com/fx-grabbed-the-first-place-while-sulli-absent-from-the-show/15043|website=koreabizwire.com|publisher=Kobiz Media Co.|accessdate=February 3, 2015}}</ref> SM Entertainment explained that she was sick and thus unable to perform. However, when she did not appear in the next few ''Red Light'' promotions and f(x)'s Korean promotion schedule was abruptly cleared for the rest of the month, it led to speculation that Sulli would be leaving the group, or that the group itself would be disbanding.<ref name=kpopstarz>{{cite web|last1=Kuang|first1=Robert|title=Fans Fear f(x) Disbandment Due To Sulli's Absence And SM Contract Expiration|url=http://www.kpopstarz.com/articles/100787/20140724/f-x-sulli-disband.htm |website=Kpopstarz |publisher= |accessdate=February 3, 2015}}</ref>  On July 24, SM Entertainment posted an official statement on the group's homepage, saytating that Sulli had become \"mentally and physically exhausted from the continuous, malicious comments and false rumors\" that had been spread about her,<ref name=kdramastars>{{cite web|last1=Jones|first1=Julie|title=Rumors Force Sulli To Take A Break From Performing|url=http://www.kdramastars.com/articles/30369/20140725/rumors-force-sulli-to-take-a-break-from-performing.htm|website=Kdramastars|publisher= |accessdate=February 3, 2015}}</ref> and would take a temporary break from the entertainment industry, while remaining a member of f(x).<ref name=mwave1>{{cite web|last1=Jung|first1=Ha-soo|title=SM Releases Official Statement Announcing f(x) Sulli Will Stop All Promotional Activities|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/71691/fx-sulli-to-halt-all-promotional-activities-for-now|website=MWave|publisher=[[CJ E&M]]|accessdate=July 25, 2014}}</ref> The remaining members would move their activities to focus on solo ventures and continued overseas activities without Sulli for the time being.<ref name=osen>{{cite web|title=\uc124\ub9ac, \ub2f9\ubd84\uac04 \uc5f0\uc608\ud65c\ub3d9 \uc270\ub2e4..\"\uc545\ud50c-\ub8e8\uba38\ub85c \uace0\ud1b5\"|url=http://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=shm&sid1=106&oid=109&aid=0002837527|website=Naver|publisher=Osen|accessdate=February 3, 2015}}</ref>\n\nSulli eventually withdrew from the group on August 8, 2015, making ''Red Light'' her final contribution.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=241&aid=0002450373 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-09-15 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20150808032623/http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=241&aid=0002450373 |archivedate=August 8, 2015 |df=mdy-all }}<br>- http://news.nate.com/view/20150807n21599?mid=n0107</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n[[Fuse (TV channel)|Fuse TV]] described f(x) as the K-Pop's top hipsters,<ref name=fuse1>{{cite web|last1=Benjamin|first1=Jeff|title=f(x) Are K-Pop's Top Hipsters With New Single \"Red Light\"|url=http://www.fuse.tv/2014/07/fx-red-light-mv-video|website=Fuse.tv|publisher=Fuse Networks|accessdate=July 3, 2014}}</ref> and the album was acclaimed by the critics. The \"Red Light\" music video reached more than 2 million views on YouTube on the first day of release.<ref name=herald>{{cite web|last1=Jackson|first1=Julie|title=f(x)\u2019s \u2018Red Light\u2019 video surpasses 2m hits on first day|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20140704000713 |website=Korea Herald|publisher=Herald Corporation|accessdate=July 4, 2014}}</ref> By August 2014, it had reached more than 10 million views.<ref name=mtsn>{{cite web|title=f(x) '\ub808\ub4dc\ub77c\uc774\ud2b8' \ubba4\ube44, \ud55c\ub2ec\ubcf4\ub984\ub9cc '1000\ub9cc\ubdf0' \ub3cc\ud30c|url=http://news.naver.com/main/ranking/read.nhn?mid=etc&sid1=111&rankingType=popular_day&oid=108&aid=0002329259&date=20140817&type=1&rankingSectionId=106&rankingSeq=21|website=Naver|publisher=Money Today Star News|accessdate=August 17, 2014}}</ref> The song \"Red Light\" was chosen by Fuse TV as one of 15 nominees for 2014's summer anthem.<ref name=fuse2>{{cite web|title=15 Tracks Poised to Become Surprise Song of the Summer|url=http://www.fuse.tv/2014/07/song-of-summer-surprise-anthems#13|website=Fuse.tv|publisher=Fuse Networks|accessdate=July 18, 2014}}</ref>\n\nThe title track \"Red Light\" was included on the lists of best K-pop songs of 2014 by ''[[Dazed]]'' (number 9),<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.dazeddigital.com/music/article/22911/1/the-top-20-k-pop-tracks-of-2014| title=The Best K-pop of 2014| work=[[Dazed]]| first=Taylor| last=Glasby| accessdate=April 3, 2016}}</ref> ''[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]'' (number 4),<ref>{{cite web| url=http://noisey.vice.com/blog/the-20-best-k-pop-songs-of-2014| title=The 20 Best K-Pop Songs of 2014| work=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]| first=Jakob| last=Dorof| date=December 29, 2014| accessdate=April 3, 2016}}</ref> and [[PopMatters]] (number one).<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.popmatters.com/feature/189085-the-best-k-pop-of-2014/P2/| title=The Best K-pop of 2014| publisher= |website=[[PopMatters]]| first=Scott |last=Interrante| date=December 23, 2014| accessdate=April 3, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Controversies===\nThe South Korean broadcast station [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS]] ruled \"Red Light\" unfit for broadcast, since the song mentions a specific brand, the heavy equipment manufacturing company [[Caterpillar Inc.|Caterpillar]].<ref name=cat>{{cite web|title=KBS Deems f(x)\u2019s New Title Song \"Red Light\" Unfit for Broadcast, MBC Still Undecided|url=http://www.soompi.com/2014/07/01/kbs-deems-fxs-new-title-song-red-light-unfit-for-broadcast-mbc-still-undecided|website=Soompi|publisher= |accessdate=July 2, 2014}}</ref> In response, the f(x)'s agency, SM Entertainment, modified the lyrics.<ref name=cat2>{{cite web|title=f(x) Modifies \"Red Light\" Lyrics, KBS Gives Them the Green Light|url=http://www.soompi.com/2014/07/03/fx-modifies-red-light-lyrics-kbs-gives-them-the-green-light|website=Soompi|publisher= |accessdate=July 3, 2014}}</ref> Other TV stations, however, such as [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]]'s ''[[The Music Trend|Inkigayo]]'', [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]'s [[Show Champion]] and [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]]'s M!Countdown, allowed broadcast of the song with its original lyrics. {{cn|date=March 2020}}\n\n==Track listing==\n{{tracklist\n| collapsed       = \n| headline        =\n| extra_column    = <!--Notes-->\n| total length    =\n| title1          = Red Light\n| lyrics1         = Kenzie\n| music1          = Bryan Jarett, Daniel Ullmann, [[Phrased Differently|Maegan Cottone]],  Allison Kaplan, Sherry St. Germain, /  Produced by Casper & B.\n| length1         = 3:32\n| title2          = MILK\n| lyrics2         = Kenzie\n| music2          = Lee Hyun Seung, [[Kenzie_(songwriter)|Kenzie]], [[Teddy Riley]], DOM, [[Engelina|Engelina Larsen]]\n| length2         = 3:36\n| title3          =  Butterfly\n| note3 = \ub098\ube44; ''Nabi''\n| lyrics3         =  Shin Jin Hye (Jam Factory)\n| music3          = [[Thomas Troelsen]], Engelina Larsen, Shin Eun Seung (Hitchhiker)\n| length3         = 2:57\n| title4          =  Rainbow\n| note4 = \ubb34\uc9c0\uac1c; ''Mujigae''\n| lyrics4         = [[Misfit (songwriter)|Misfit]]\n| music4          = Will Simms / Ylva Dimberg\n| length4         = 2:47\n| title5          = All Night\n| lyrics5         =